WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.569 --> 00:00:04.902
[Crow caws]

2
00:00:04.972 --> 00:00:07.305
Frankie: <i>There's a lot of firsts</i>
i <i>in people's lives...</i>

3
00:00:07.374 --> 00:00:10.242
<i>First tooth. first birthday.
first steps.</i>

4
00:00:10.310 --> 00:00:13.542
<i>first day of school.
and first day of a real job.</i>

5
00:00:13.814 --> 00:00:14.543
[Camera shutter clicks]

6
00:00:14.815 --> 00:00:17.182
Whaaaaat are you doing?

7
00:00:17.251 --> 00:00:20.244
I knew you wouldn't let me take
your picture in the morning.

8
00:00:20.320 --> 00:00:21.788
so I thought I'd do it now.

9
00:00:21.855 --> 00:00:24.324
Oh. and since you're up.
will you hold this sign?

10
00:00:25.859 --> 00:00:27.828
[Camera shutter clicks]
- Ow! Stop!

11
00:00:27.895 --> 00:00:30.387
You're gonna wake Brick up.
His dream world is all he's got.

12
00:00:30.464 --> 00:00:32.365
No. Brick fell asleep
on the couch again.

13
00:00:32.432 --> 00:00:34.833
Your dad had on basketball.
Knocked him right out.

14
00:00:34.902 --> 00:00:38.896
So. I know you're. like. a sales
rep for a plumbing company.

15
00:00:38.972 --> 00:00:42.170
but do you drive around
and sell plumbing stuff.

16
00:00:42.242 --> 00:00:44.177
or do you have to call people?

17
00:00:44.244 --> 00:00:46.941
It helps me to brag about your
new job if I know what it is.

18
00:00:47.014 --> 00:00:48.380
I don't know.

19
00:00:48.448 --> 00:00:50.248
I know I'm training
with some guy named Dwayne

20
00:00:50.284 --> 00:00:51.895
for a couple weeks.
He's gonna show me the ropes.

21
00:00:51.919 --> 00:00:53.979
Aww!
Look at you all grown up!

22
00:00:54.054 --> 00:00:55.522
[Chuckles]

23
00:00:55.589 --> 00:00:57.867
Hey. you want me to rub your
back like when you were little?

24
00:00:57.891 --> 00:00:58.984
No!

25
00:00:59.059 --> 00:01:01.221
Actually. okay.

26
00:01:01.295 --> 00:01:03.890
Oh. ho. ho. ho.

27
00:01:03.964 --> 00:01:05.489
So. we never had a chance

28
00:01:05.566 --> 00:01:08.035
to talk about
the New Year's Eve party.

29
00:01:08.101 --> 00:01:09.379
I know
you were at your Grandpa's.

30
00:01:09.403 --> 00:01:13.238
but let's just say things
happened.

31
00:01:13.307 --> 00:01:15.435
Look. lot of weird stuff
went down on New Year's.

32
00:01:15.509 --> 00:01:17.205
I don't get it.
I'll never get it.

33
00:01:17.277 --> 00:01:19.212
I don't want to get it.
Staying out of it.

34
00:01:19.279 --> 00:01:20.577
Okay. okay.

35
00:01:20.647 --> 00:01:23.515
Hey. you want me to make you
a lunch for tomorrow?

36
00:01:23.584 --> 00:01:26.383
Mom. like I told you
the first day of first grade.

37
00:01:26.453 --> 00:01:27.978
get out of my room.

38
00:01:28.055 --> 00:01:29.853
[Chuckles] Oh.

39
00:01:29.923 --> 00:01:32.119
♪♪♪♪

40
00:01:32.192 --> 00:01:34.855
PB&J!
Crust on. no note.

41
00:01:34.928 --> 00:01:37.227
Well. it's my first day.
Maybe a note.

42
00:01:37.297 --> 00:01:39.163
[Camera shutter clicks]

43
00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:41.996
Twist right.
[Grunts]

44
00:01:42.069 --> 00:01:44.129
So. Sean never called
or texted or anything

45
00:01:44.204 --> 00:01:45.228
since New Year's Eve?

46
00:01:45.305 --> 00:01:46.637
No. And why would he?

47
00:01:46.907 --> 00:01:48.418
I mean. the last thing he saw
was me kissing Aidan.

48
00:01:48.442 --> 00:01:50.070
[Sighs] I don't know.

49
00:01:50.143 --> 00:01:51.921
Maybe Hecks and Donahues just
aren't meant to be together.

50
00:01:51.945 --> 00:01:53.456
Hey. at least you got kissed
on New Year's.

51
00:01:53.480 --> 00:01:55.312
That's one more kiss than I got.

52
00:01:55.382 --> 00:01:57.160
if you don't count the old lady
who thought I was Clay Aiken.

53
00:01:57.184 --> 00:01:59.153
Oh.
"BTdubs." Aidan's
nothing to sneeze at.

54
00:01:59.219 --> 00:02:00.949
He's really cute.
Twist left.
Yeah.

55
00:02:01.021 --> 00:02:04.981
No. no. no. he's totally cute.
and we have fun together.

56
00:02:05.058 --> 00:02:08.495
But. you know. Sean's kiss
was like. "Ahh!"

57
00:02:08.562 --> 00:02:10.929
And Aidan's kiss
is like. "Eh."

58
00:02:10.998 --> 00:02:13.968
Listen to me. you are 10 years
too young to settle for "eh."

59
00:02:14.034 --> 00:02:16.435
Until things start sagging.
you hold out for "ah."

60
00:02:16.503 --> 00:02:19.063
[Sighs] You're right.
you're right. I know.

61
00:02:19.139 --> 00:02:22.234
If I'm not feeling it with
Aidan. I should end things now.

62
00:02:22.309 --> 00:02:24.574
[Sighs] It's not fair
to string him along.

63
00:02:24.645 --> 00:02:26.375
- Mm.
- [Groans]

64
00:02:26.446 --> 00:02:30.178
It's just you know how terrible
I am at breaking up with people.

65
00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:31.582
I mean. look at me with Jeremy.

66
00:02:31.652 --> 00:02:33.211
- Mm.
- And this is what's sad...

67
00:02:33.286 --> 00:02:35.414
The guys that want me.
I don't want.

68
00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:38.254
and the guy I want disappears
after kissing me.

69
00:02:38.325 --> 00:02:40.021
Well. no one's gonna kiss you

70
00:02:40.093 --> 00:02:41.604
with that little pity-party
you're throwing yourself.

71
00:02:41.628 --> 00:02:43.927
So lace up your big-girl
breakup boots and get 'er done.

72
00:02:45.432 --> 00:02:47.560
Right.

73
00:02:47.634 --> 00:02:49.603
Axl: We just walked out
with the account.

74
00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:52.071
and all because I noticed
the owner was a Cub fan.

75
00:02:52.139 --> 00:02:53.334
Dwayne was blown away.

76
00:02:53.407 --> 00:02:54.568
Man. that's great.

77
00:02:54.641 --> 00:02:56.303
On the first day.
I can't believe it!

78
00:02:56.376 --> 00:02:57.503
What?
Can't believe what?

79
00:02:57.577 --> 00:02:59.102
And then he says
he doesn't think

80
00:02:59.179 --> 00:03:00.556
I'm gonna even need the whole
two weeks of training.

81
00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:02.125
Says I could be flying
solo by Thursday.

82
00:03:02.149 --> 00:03:03.412
That's my boy.

83
00:03:05.686 --> 00:03:08.053
So. tell me all about it.
Start at the beginning.

84
00:03:08.121 --> 00:03:10.352
Uch. I am fried.
I just told Dad the whole story.

85
00:03:10.424 --> 00:03:11.983
He'll tell you.
- No. he won't.

86
00:03:12.059 --> 00:03:13.083
Probably not.

87
00:03:13.160 --> 00:03:14.337
Just tell me what Dwayne said.

88
00:03:14.361 --> 00:03:15.954
Look it's all good. all right?

89
00:03:16.029 --> 00:03:18.089
I'm gonna crash.
Thanks for the advice. Dad.

90
00:03:18.165 --> 00:03:19.565
More where that came from.

91
00:03:19.633 --> 00:03:22.193
Yeah. I'm here if you need me.

92
00:03:22.269 --> 00:03:24.033
I-I'm in sales. too.

93
00:03:24.104 --> 00:03:26.315
Today I sold some guy teeth
whitening that he didn't need.

94
00:03:26.339 --> 00:03:27.684
Oh. once. I accidentally
sold a c...

95
00:03:27.708 --> 00:03:29.734
[Door slams]

96
00:03:30.010 --> 00:03:31.603
♪♪♪♪

97
00:03:31.678 --> 00:03:33.374
Tell him later.

98
00:03:35.682 --> 00:03:39.016
[Upbeat pop-rock music plays]

99
00:03:39.086 --> 00:03:44.582
♪♪♪♪

100
00:03:44.658 --> 00:03:45.658
Thank you!

101
00:03:45.692 --> 00:03:48.491
[Tepid applause]

102
00:03:48.562 --> 00:03:51.157
Thank you. Your smattering of
applause is why we do it.

103
00:03:51.231 --> 00:03:52.665
[Chuckles]
Hey. come on. guys.

104
00:03:52.733 --> 00:03:54.201
- Oh!
- [Gasps]

105
00:03:54.267 --> 00:03:56.395
[Feedback]
Oh. [Sighs]

106
00:03:56.470 --> 00:03:59.497
Uch. Brad. my stomach
is all fluttery...

107
00:03:59.573 --> 00:04:01.217
And not the good kind
like when you realize

108
00:04:01.241 --> 00:04:02.385
you're the only one
on the ballot

109
00:04:02.409 --> 00:04:04.105
for Youth Group Treasurer.
- Mm.

110
00:04:04.177 --> 00:04:05.755
Maybe this isn't the right time
to break up with him.

111
00:04:05.779 --> 00:04:08.078
Or maybe it's the perfect time.

112
00:04:08.148 --> 00:04:09.358
Maybe he just hit his head
so hard

113
00:04:09.382 --> 00:04:10.593
he won't remember he likes you.

114
00:04:10.617 --> 00:04:12.245
Ohh.
- Aidan: Hey. guys.

115
00:04:12.319 --> 00:04:14.618
Sue. you remember Luke?
Brad. this is our drummer.

116
00:04:14.688 --> 00:04:16.316
Well. the sticks
probably gave it away.

117
00:04:16.389 --> 00:04:17.652
[Chuckles]
Luke. this is Brad.

118
00:04:17.724 --> 00:04:18.724
How's it going?

119
00:04:18.759 --> 00:04:21.251
Good. Really good.

120
00:04:21.328 --> 00:04:23.490
Well. we played
three whole hours.

121
00:04:23.563 --> 00:04:26.089
so let's go cash in
our drink coupon.

122
00:04:26.166 --> 00:04:27.566
Be right back.
- Okay.

123
00:04:27.634 --> 00:04:30.570
Bye. [Chuckles]

124
00:04:30.637 --> 00:04:32.697
- [Inhales sharply]
- You can't break up with him.

125
00:04:32.773 --> 00:04:33.773
Mm?

126
00:04:35.776 --> 00:04:38.371
What? Brad. you were
the one who told me

127
00:04:38.445 --> 00:04:40.311
to break it off with Aidan.

128
00:04:40.380 --> 00:04:41.712
Now you're telling me I can't?

129
00:04:41.782 --> 00:04:43.717
Um. hello?
Did you not see his friend?

130
00:04:43.784 --> 00:04:46.379
'Cause I did. He is adorable.
Come on. Sue.

131
00:04:46.453 --> 00:04:48.413
You just have to go out
with Aidan a little longer

132
00:04:48.455 --> 00:04:50.455
so I can get to know
this Luke guy a little better.

133
00:04:50.490 --> 00:04:52.356
No. Brad.
I couldn't do that to Aidan.

134
00:04:52.425 --> 00:04:53.825
[Scoffs]
Just wouldn't be right.

135
00:04:54.094 --> 00:04:55.460
Please? You owe me.

136
00:04:55.529 --> 00:04:57.555
Oh. I can't believe
there's a hot gay drummer

137
00:04:57.631 --> 00:04:59.725
in Aidan's band.
And you kept it to yourself.

138
00:04:59.800 --> 00:05:01.325
Oh. well. I don't know.

139
00:05:01.401 --> 00:05:03.279
I didn't want to be that kind of
person who was like.

140
00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:05.534
"You're gay. he's gay.
therefore I should set you up."

141
00:05:05.605 --> 00:05:07.471
Why not? Sue.
Gumford is not exactly

142
00:05:07.541 --> 00:05:08.736
the Fire Island of Indiana.

143
00:05:08.809 --> 00:05:10.437
It's slim pickings out there.

144
00:05:10.510 --> 00:05:12.479
Sorry. I didn't know
the protocol.

145
00:05:12.546 --> 00:05:14.344
Ah. so you're really ready
to start dating?

146
00:05:14.414 --> 00:05:16.406
Of course I am.
It's just tough in college.

147
00:05:16.483 --> 00:05:18.384
All the good gay guys
are taken by girls.

148
00:05:18.451 --> 00:05:20.051
- Ah. yeah.
- In New York. it was easier.

149
00:05:20.120 --> 00:05:21.679
But you get outside of New York.

150
00:05:21.755 --> 00:05:23.699
and there's still places that
wouldn't bake me a wedding cake.

151
00:05:23.723 --> 00:05:27.091
That is just not right. Brad.
Everybody deserves cake.

152
00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:28.389
- Thank you.
- Okay.

153
00:05:28.461 --> 00:05:30.206
I'm not gonna break it off
with Aidan just yet.

154
00:05:30.230 --> 00:05:31.808
but I feel like he's just gonna
look at my face

155
00:05:31.832 --> 00:05:33.425
and know that something is up.

156
00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:35.492
Sue. you were the Girl
in the Well at Dollywood.

157
00:05:35.569 --> 00:05:37.663
and you audited two
student-taught improv classes.

158
00:05:37.737 --> 00:05:39.537
Don't let that top-notch
training go to waste.

159
00:05:39.573 --> 00:05:41.599
Yeah. Okay.

160
00:05:41.675 --> 00:05:44.372
- Mm!
- Oh. my God!

161
00:05:44.444 --> 00:05:46.743
[Mike and Axl laughing]

162
00:05:46.813 --> 00:05:49.339
Oh. there you guys are.
I was starting to get worried.

163
00:05:49.416 --> 00:05:52.386
Yeah. well. Axl texted and said
that he had a sales call

164
00:05:52.452 --> 00:05:54.250
on Route 42.
and I was right there.

165
00:05:54.321 --> 00:05:55.832
Yeah. and then Dad
texted me back and said.

166
00:05:55.856 --> 00:05:57.586
"Meet me at Goobers.
It's fried fish night."

167
00:05:57.657 --> 00:05:59.216
Who's saying no to that?

168
00:05:59.292 --> 00:06:01.625
Well. I guess you have to
get a chance to say no.

169
00:06:01.695 --> 00:06:04.255
Anyway. I'm glad you guys are
getting each other's texts.

170
00:06:04.331 --> 00:06:06.576
I guess you missed mine where
I said. "Mike. where are you?

171
00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:08.535
Are we getting dinner?
Do you know where Axl is?"

172
00:06:08.602 --> 00:06:10.400
And. Axl. I texted you.
"Axl. where are you?

173
00:06:10.470 --> 00:06:12.582
Are we getting dinner?
Do you know where your dad is?"

174
00:06:12.606 --> 00:06:14.871
Uh. though you probably
didn't hear your phones.

175
00:06:14.941 --> 00:06:17.342
Goobers is loud.
But I'm glad you guys had fun.

176
00:06:17.410 --> 00:06:19.641
Yeah. we did... once we got
out of the parking lot.

177
00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:21.272
Oh. what happened
in the parking lot?

178
00:06:21.348 --> 00:06:22.543
- Um...
- Nothing.

179
00:06:22.616 --> 00:06:24.551
It'd take too long to explain.

180
00:06:24.618 --> 00:06:26.246
- I got time.
- Uh. no. he's right.

181
00:06:26.319 --> 00:06:28.345
You had to be there.
- Yeah. but I wasn't there.

182
00:06:28.421 --> 00:06:29.821
That's why I need you
to tell me.

183
00:06:29.890 --> 00:06:31.791
Eh. it's an inside joke.

184
00:06:31.858 --> 00:06:33.793
[Sighs]

185
00:06:33.860 --> 00:06:36.455
They're all inside jokes to me.

186
00:06:41.434 --> 00:06:43.346
Well. Luke. um. I don't
know if you know this.

187
00:06:43.370 --> 00:06:46.340
but Brad is actually
also a performer.

188
00:06:46.406 --> 00:06:49.418
He is an amazing singer/dancer.

189
00:06:49.442 --> 00:06:50.569
Isn't that right. Brad?

190
00:06:52.879 --> 00:06:55.610
Anyway. um. if I can speak
for Brad...

191
00:06:55.682 --> 00:06:58.413
Which apparently I have to...
[Laughs]

192
00:06:58.485 --> 00:07:00.454
Brad has an amazing voice.

193
00:07:00.520 --> 00:07:02.887
He is the star of
our no-cut a cappella group.

194
00:07:02.956 --> 00:07:05.448
I mean. it's no cut.
but even if it were cut.

195
00:07:05.525 --> 00:07:07.858
he would make the cut.
[Laughs]

196
00:07:07.928 --> 00:07:10.261
It's like they think
red pepper is so dangerous

197
00:07:10.330 --> 00:07:12.196
they have to make it
impossible to open.

198
00:07:12.265 --> 00:07:13.665
- [Gasps] Aah!
- Oh. my God.

199
00:07:13.733 --> 00:07:15.361
Oh. I'm so sorry. Sue.

200
00:07:15.435 --> 00:07:16.869
No. don't touch it!

201
00:07:16.937 --> 00:07:19.771
Uh. if I just [Clears throat]
keep my eye closed.

202
00:07:19.839 --> 00:07:21.364
I'll be fine.

203
00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:22.919
[Chuckles] No. anyway...
Nope. not working.

204
00:07:22.943 --> 00:07:24.809
Got to get water involved.
- Go. go. go. go.

205
00:07:24.878 --> 00:07:27.609
[Breathing sharply]
- Ohh.

206
00:07:27.681 --> 00:07:29.877
Sue. I'm so sorry.

207
00:07:29.950 --> 00:07:31.384
[Water running]

208
00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:33.750
Oh. shoot. Aidan.
We got to go.

209
00:07:33.820 --> 00:07:35.482
We're gonna be late
for our gig at Sig Ep.

210
00:07:35.555 --> 00:07:37.786
I don't know. I should
probably stay here with Sue.

211
00:07:37.857 --> 00:07:39.416
No. No. no. no.

212
00:07:39.492 --> 00:07:42.621
Uh. go. Go. go.
You need that $5.

213
00:07:42.696 --> 00:07:46.758
♪♪♪♪

214
00:07:46.833 --> 00:07:48.597
[Door opens]

215
00:07:48.668 --> 00:07:49.761
[Chuckles]

216
00:07:49.836 --> 00:07:50.963
[Door closes]

217
00:07:51.037 --> 00:07:52.471
Brad. what is
the matter with you?!

218
00:07:52.539 --> 00:07:53.700
What?

219
00:07:53.773 --> 00:07:56.436
You were so boring!
Where is Brad?

220
00:07:56.509 --> 00:07:58.705
You were like the shell of Brad
with no Brad inside.

221
00:07:58.778 --> 00:08:00.679
Oh. I'm sorry.
When I get nervous. I shut down.

222
00:08:00.747 --> 00:08:01.908
The same thing happens to me

223
00:08:01.982 --> 00:08:03.473
when I get around
my improv coach.

224
00:08:03.550 --> 00:08:05.550
He was David James Elliott's
stunt double on "JAG."

225
00:08:05.585 --> 00:08:07.247
Yeah. that "JAG."

226
00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:09.482
Okay. well. I have practically
lost 70% of the vision

227
00:08:09.556 --> 00:08:11.889
in one of my eyes. so if you're
not gonna start bringing it

228
00:08:11.958 --> 00:08:13.586
and get this thing going
with Luke.

229
00:08:13.660 --> 00:08:15.253
I am going to tell Aidan
the truth.

230
00:08:15.328 --> 00:08:17.448
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Just give me a little more time.

231
00:08:17.497 --> 00:08:19.762
[Sighs] Have I told you
you're the most amazing person

232
00:08:19.833 --> 00:08:21.392
and I would be lost without you?

233
00:08:21.468 --> 00:08:23.630
- Yeah. save it for Luke.
- Okay.

234
00:08:23.703 --> 00:08:25.763
♪♪♪♪

235
00:08:25.839 --> 00:08:27.467
[Television plays]

236
00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:29.566
<i>And with that.
they are now up by 7 points.</i>

237
00:08:29.642 --> 00:08:31.474
Hey. Whatcha doing?

238
00:08:31.544 --> 00:08:32.842
'Cause I was thinking

239
00:08:32.912 --> 00:08:34.676
we could finally start
"The Walking Dead."

240
00:08:34.748 --> 00:08:36.774
Oh. yeah. Sorry.

241
00:08:36.850 --> 00:08:39.684
I'm already about seven
episodes in with Axl.

242
00:08:39.753 --> 00:08:41.346
What?

243
00:08:41.421 --> 00:08:43.447
I have been waiting for you.

244
00:08:43.523 --> 00:08:45.685
We've been talking about
watching this for months.

245
00:08:45.759 --> 00:08:47.728
I know. but you and I
could never figure out

246
00:08:47.794 --> 00:08:49.695
how to make the thing come on.
- [Sighs]

247
00:08:49.763 --> 00:08:51.561
And then Axl came
and fiddled with it.

248
00:08:51.631 --> 00:08:53.623
and. next thing we know.
we were watching it.

249
00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:55.220
I can't believe
you didn't come get me.

250
00:08:55.335 --> 00:08:56.946
Well. sorry.
We didn't know where you were.

251
00:08:56.970 --> 00:08:58.871
We couldn't find you.
- [Scoffs] Really?

252
00:08:58.938 --> 00:09:00.804
'Cause the house
is like five feet wide.

253
00:09:00.874 --> 00:09:02.433
Okay. we didn't try.

254
00:09:02.509 --> 00:09:04.569
But. hey. now you don't
have to worry about me.

255
00:09:04.644 --> 00:09:06.510
Just watch it
whenever you feel like it.

256
00:09:06.579 --> 00:09:07.979
[Sighs]

257
00:09:08.048 --> 00:09:10.415
<i>Frankie: So. Mike and Axl had
found each other again.</i>

258
00:09:10.483 --> 00:09:12.509
<i>and I was genuinely happy
for them...</i>

259
00:09:12.585 --> 00:09:14.520
<i>until I wasn't.</i>

260
00:09:14.587 --> 00:09:17.421
[Door closes]
I was like. "That's a really
hairy armadillo. my friend."

261
00:09:17.490 --> 00:09:19.101
[Chuckles]
He didn't even know what to say.

262
00:09:19.125 --> 00:09:21.822
Ooh. Taco Jason's.
What'd you get me?

263
00:09:21.895 --> 00:09:23.761
Uh...

264
00:09:23.830 --> 00:09:25.321
Seriously?

265
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:28.027
W... You weren't with us.
We didn't think.

266
00:09:28.101 --> 00:09:30.400
It was really just
a last-minute thing.

267
00:09:30.470 --> 00:09:32.405
It's 6:30. and you didn't
bother to check in.

268
00:09:32.472 --> 00:09:33.735
You just went to Taco Jason's

269
00:09:33.807 --> 00:09:35.400
and got something
for yourselves.

270
00:09:35.475 --> 00:09:37.376
[Muffled] We didn't
know you'd want anything.

271
00:09:37.444 --> 00:09:39.777
[Sighs]
Okay. Fine.

272
00:09:39.846 --> 00:09:42.748
Let's just clear up
any confusion.

273
00:09:42.816 --> 00:09:45.012
In the future. if you are
ever out somewhere

274
00:09:45.085 --> 00:09:47.884
getting food at dinnertime.
I would like to be included.

275
00:09:47.954 --> 00:09:50.719
And while we're at it.
if I am ever drowning

276
00:09:50.790 --> 00:09:52.884
in the ocean.
please pull me out.

277
00:09:52.959 --> 00:09:55.485
And if you ever step over what
appears to be my dead body.

278
00:09:55.562 --> 00:09:56.621
please take my pulse.

279
00:09:56.696 --> 00:09:58.062
Want some of my burrito?

280
00:09:58.131 --> 00:10:00.396
No. I don't want the burrito!
It's too spicy.

281
00:10:00.467 --> 00:10:02.026
I like the Quesadilla Gringo.

282
00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:04.542
which I would have ordered if
anybody had bothered to call me.

283
00:10:04.604 --> 00:10:10.043
♪♪♪♪

284
00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:11.510
So. I was
the understudy for Snoopy.

285
00:10:11.578 --> 00:10:12.773
I didn't get the lead.

286
00:10:12.846 --> 00:10:14.371
But then. the guy
who got it got busted

287
00:10:14.447 --> 00:10:15.891
for stealing a can of SlimFast
at the drugstore.

288
00:10:15.915 --> 00:10:17.593
So he's being arraigned.
and guess who got the part.

289
00:10:17.617 --> 00:10:19.415
If you're gonna guess me.
you'd be right.

290
00:10:19.486 --> 00:10:21.648
Oh. Oh. hey. Brad. why don't
I take the cup of coffee

291
00:10:21.721 --> 00:10:26.056
and you take my nice relaxing
cup of chamomile tea.

292
00:10:26.126 --> 00:10:28.170
Ooh. I love chamomile tea!
Actually. I love all teas.

293
00:10:28.194 --> 00:10:30.390
Chamomile. Chamomile.
That's a weird word. isn't it?

294
00:10:30.463 --> 00:10:31.897
My grandma always
drinks chamomile.

295
00:10:31.965 --> 00:10:33.909
[Chuckles] Do you have
a grandma? I love my grandma.

296
00:10:33.933 --> 00:10:35.526
I also think she really...
- Look out.

297
00:10:35.602 --> 00:10:37.537
- [Gasps]
- Dude. watch it!

298
00:10:37.604 --> 00:10:39.004
Can you believe that?

299
00:10:39.072 --> 00:10:40.870
[Gasps] Oh. oh.

300
00:10:40.940 --> 00:10:41.940
Ohh.

301
00:10:42.008 --> 00:10:43.670
[Gasping]

302
00:10:49.983 --> 00:10:51.827
[Muffled] Ugh. So. he took
me to the emergency room

303
00:10:51.851 --> 00:10:53.581
because my nose
wouldn't stop bleeding.

304
00:10:53.653 --> 00:10:56.555
And then. when we were leaving.
he shut the door on my hand.

305
00:10:56.623 --> 00:10:59.889
- Oh. my God.
- Yeah. it's getting bad. Brad.

306
00:10:59.959 --> 00:11:02.451
What's the deal with Luke?
Are you making any progress?

307
00:11:02.529 --> 00:11:04.828
'Cause I got to break up
with Aidan before he kills me.

308
00:11:04.898 --> 00:11:07.129
I'm trying. I just get
so nervous around him.

309
00:11:07.200 --> 00:11:10.500
I got to find my sweet spot...
Somewhere between total shutdown

310
00:11:10.570 --> 00:11:13.096
and blathering on about proper
tap-shoe maintenance.

311
00:11:13.173 --> 00:11:15.836
Why didn't you stop me?
- I tried!

312
00:11:15.909 --> 00:11:18.105
Okay. look. Brad. if you would
just be yourself.

313
00:11:18.178 --> 00:11:19.510
I know he would love you.

314
00:11:19.579 --> 00:11:21.104
Oh. I know. I know!

315
00:11:21.181 --> 00:11:22.911
I just can't tell
if he's being nice to me

316
00:11:22.982 --> 00:11:24.902
'cause I'm your friend
or 'cause he's interested.

317
00:11:24.951 --> 00:11:26.715
I just need a few more days
to suss him out.

318
00:11:26.786 --> 00:11:28.687
I may not have a few more days!

319
00:11:28.755 --> 00:11:31.452
We are going to a fondue
restaurant tomorrow.

320
00:11:31.524 --> 00:11:34.926
That is fire and pokey forks.

321
00:11:34.994 --> 00:11:36.622
Ugh!

322
00:11:38.131 --> 00:11:40.032
You hungry?
Let's go grab some dinner.

323
00:11:40.099 --> 00:11:42.159
What?
Hold on. Me and you?

324
00:11:42.235 --> 00:11:43.533
Just the two of us?

325
00:11:43.603 --> 00:11:44.798
Yeah.
Where you want to go?

326
00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:48.501
Oh. Um.
I would love a burger.

327
00:11:48.575 --> 00:11:50.737
And there's a new place
Hole Lotta Burger.

328
00:11:50.810 --> 00:11:52.073
but they spell it H-O-L-E

329
00:11:52.145 --> 00:11:53.670
because there's a hole
in the middle

330
00:11:53.746 --> 00:11:54.941
and they fill it with cheese.

331
00:11:55.014 --> 00:11:56.539
Get it? The "hole"
has two meanings.

332
00:11:56.616 --> 00:11:58.050
I get it.
Let's go. Let's do it.

333
00:11:58.117 --> 00:11:59.551
Grab your purse.
You're paying.

334
00:11:59.619 --> 00:12:01.130
Okay. just got to get out
of these scrubs

335
00:12:01.154 --> 00:12:03.199
and put on a fresh layer
of deodorant. and I'm ready.

336
00:12:03.223 --> 00:12:05.590
Meet you in the car.

337
00:12:12.098 --> 00:12:14.090
Hey.
Look who just got home.

338
00:12:14.167 --> 00:12:15.829
Let's go! I'm starving!

339
00:12:15.902 --> 00:12:17.268
But. Axl. you're in my seat.

340
00:12:17.537 --> 00:12:18.971
Mom. don't make a big deal.

341
00:12:19.038 --> 00:12:21.200
The seat belt works better
up here. and I'm young.

342
00:12:21.274 --> 00:12:22.173
Let's just go.

343
00:12:22.242 --> 00:12:24.677
[Sighs] Fine.
Fine.

344
00:12:24.744 --> 00:12:26.736
[Clears throat]
I'm starving. too.

345
00:12:26.813 --> 00:12:29.578
Just get a burger in my mouth.
and I will be happy.

346
00:12:29.649 --> 00:12:31.049
No!
I had a burger for lunch.

347
00:12:31.117 --> 00:12:32.016
I want Chinese.

348
00:12:32.085 --> 00:12:33.917
He had a burger for lunch.

349
00:12:33.987 --> 00:12:35.631
Wait a minute.
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

350
00:12:35.655 --> 00:12:37.055
I thought we agreed on burgers?

351
00:12:37.123 --> 00:12:39.615
You lost the popular vote. Mom.
two to one. Get over it.

352
00:12:39.692 --> 00:12:41.251
I'm sorry.
Was I talking to you?

353
00:12:41.327 --> 00:12:43.990
No. I was talking to my husband.
Are you my husband?

354
00:12:44.063 --> 00:12:45.622
[Whispering loudly]
Mike.

355
00:12:45.698 --> 00:12:47.860
I thought it was gonna be
me and you and burgers.

356
00:12:47.934 --> 00:12:49.300
He's the one horning in here.

357
00:12:49.569 --> 00:12:51.129
Yeah. Frankie. he lost
an account today.

358
00:12:51.170 --> 00:12:52.968
He feels bad.
- Well. how would I know that?

359
00:12:53.039 --> 00:12:54.598
I... Nobody ever tells me
anything.

360
00:12:54.674 --> 00:12:56.142
You guys come home from work

361
00:12:56.209 --> 00:12:58.020
and get in your little
clubhouse. and I'm invisible.

362
00:12:58.044 --> 00:12:59.842
Dad says he wants Chinese.

363
00:12:59.912 --> 00:13:01.744
Yeah. oh. did he?
Did you say that. Mike?

364
00:13:01.814 --> 00:13:03.112
'Cause five minutes ago.

365
00:13:03.182 --> 00:13:04.960
you couldn't wait
to try the new burger place.

366
00:13:04.984 --> 00:13:07.010
But all of a sudden.
your little backup singer

367
00:13:07.086 --> 00:13:08.782
says you'd rather have
Chinese so...

368
00:13:08.855 --> 00:13:10.221
Oh. my God!
There she goes again!

369
00:13:10.290 --> 00:13:12.334
The great ruiner. ruining
everything fun in her path.

370
00:13:12.358 --> 00:13:13.883
Mom. Dad and I
have had tough days.

371
00:13:13.960 --> 00:13:15.588
We want egg rolls.
Just let it happen!

372
00:13:15.662 --> 00:13:17.130
[Sighs]
Hey. Axl. Come on.

373
00:13:17.196 --> 00:13:19.597
What if we got you an order
of those dumplings you like?

374
00:13:19.666 --> 00:13:21.226
I don't want dumplings!
I want a burger!

375
00:13:21.301 --> 00:13:23.236
That's why I am going
to Hole Lotta Burger...

376
00:13:23.303 --> 00:13:25.568
Not because the name is clever
and makes me laugh.

377
00:13:25.638 --> 00:13:26.901
but because that was the plan.

378
00:13:26.973 --> 00:13:28.134
You stick with the plan!

379
00:13:28.207 --> 00:13:29.732
- Frankie...
- No. I've had it.

380
00:13:29.809 --> 00:13:31.687
I don't need you guys.
I don't need any of this.

381
00:13:31.711 --> 00:13:33.839
Have fun on your date.

382
00:13:33.913 --> 00:13:36.007
♪♪♪♪

383
00:13:36.082 --> 00:13:37.778
[Sighs]

384
00:13:37.850 --> 00:13:40.342
Hey! Look who's here!
It's Brick.

385
00:13:40.620 --> 00:13:42.646
See? I've got Brick.
and we're very close.

386
00:13:42.722 --> 00:13:44.213
Hey. buddy!
- [Chuckles]

387
00:13:44.290 --> 00:13:46.919
So while you and Axl are
"bro-ing" around out there.

388
00:13:46.993 --> 00:13:48.586
Brick and I will be out. too.

389
00:13:48.661 --> 00:13:50.755
having fun and making
our own inside jokes.

390
00:13:50.830 --> 00:13:52.196
He's my backup singer.

391
00:13:52.265 --> 00:13:54.376
and we're gonna go out to dinner
and have ice cream...

392
00:13:54.400 --> 00:13:56.096
Uh. I have a lot of homework.

393
00:13:56.169 --> 00:13:58.832
[Sighs] So you guys go
and do whatever you want.

394
00:13:58.905 --> 00:14:00.999
And while you're slurping
your Don's Oriental noodles

395
00:14:01.074 --> 00:14:03.168
like "Lady and the Tramp."
just know that Brick and I

396
00:14:03.242 --> 00:14:04.710
will be at the new burger place.

397
00:14:04.777 --> 00:14:06.678
enjoying
a "Down the Rabbit Hole."

398
00:14:06.746 --> 00:14:08.339
I don't even know what that is.

399
00:14:08.414 --> 00:14:10.280
but I'm very excited
to find out!

400
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:12.046
I'd rather have Chinese.

401
00:14:12.118 --> 00:14:14.087
Brick.

402
00:14:14.153 --> 00:14:16.782
[Applause]

403
00:14:16.856 --> 00:14:18.290
Okay. Brad.

404
00:14:18.358 --> 00:14:21.055
I am only just now starting
to get vision back in my eye.

405
00:14:21.127 --> 00:14:24.097
and I would like to keep it. so
you better ask Luke out tonight.

406
00:14:24.163 --> 00:14:25.756
I know. I got this.

407
00:14:25.832 --> 00:14:27.733
The problem before
was I hadn't rehearsed.

408
00:14:27.800 --> 00:14:30.031
didn't give myself business.
some kind of space work.

409
00:14:30.103 --> 00:14:32.095
So I'm gonna casually
suggest a game of pool.

410
00:14:32.171 --> 00:14:34.265
Then I'll joke that.
if I make the next shot.

411
00:14:34.340 --> 00:14:35.968
Luke has to go out with me.
- Oh!

412
00:14:36.042 --> 00:14:38.238
That's good. And you're sure
you can make the shot?

413
00:14:38.311 --> 00:14:39.836
Oh. yeah.
I'm a pool shark.

414
00:14:39.912 --> 00:14:41.790
That's the one thing my dad
and I do together...

415
00:14:41.814 --> 00:14:42.854
That and awkward silences.

416
00:14:42.915 --> 00:14:44.110
Hey. babe.

417
00:14:44.183 --> 00:14:45.674
[Chuckles]

418
00:14:45.752 --> 00:14:48.722
Or Sue. [Chuckles]
I also go by just Sue.

419
00:14:48.788 --> 00:14:52.088
I mean. I answer to both. but.
uh. I answer to "Sue" more.

420
00:14:52.158 --> 00:14:53.649
Right.

421
00:14:53.726 --> 00:14:55.251
Oh. look!
A pool table.

422
00:14:55.328 --> 00:14:57.763
How about.
uh. me and Sue against...

423
00:14:57.830 --> 00:15:00.061
oh. right. you and Aidan?

424
00:15:00.133 --> 00:15:01.431
Cool. I'll break.

425
00:15:08.174 --> 00:15:09.267
[Gasps] Oh!

426
00:15:09.342 --> 00:15:10.401
- Oh.
- Oh. my God.

427
00:15:10.476 --> 00:15:12.672
S-Sue. I-I really didn't...

428
00:15:12.745 --> 00:15:14.441
- Ohh!
- Oh. my God.

429
00:15:14.714 --> 00:15:16.683
I'm so sorry.
H-Help!

430
00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:17.876
Can I get some help here?

431
00:15:17.950 --> 00:15:20.419
Aah!
[Panting]

432
00:15:20.486 --> 00:15:22.421
Oh.

433
00:15:29.262 --> 00:15:30.855
Mom. I'm tired.

434
00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:32.728
We've been driving
around for an hour.

435
00:15:32.799 --> 00:15:33.732
Can we just go home?

436
00:15:33.800 --> 00:15:34.995
No.

437
00:15:35.067 --> 00:15:36.412
Then are we going
to get ice cream?

438
00:15:36.436 --> 00:15:37.995
You said something
about ice cream.

439
00:15:38.070 --> 00:15:39.936
No. I just said that to make
your dad and Axl

440
00:15:40.006 --> 00:15:41.406
feel like they're missing
something.

441
00:15:41.474 --> 00:15:43.102
I don't think
that's going to happen.

442
00:15:43.176 --> 00:15:44.474
I'm pretty low
on the totem pole.

443
00:15:44.744 --> 00:15:46.269
- [Sighs]
- So then what are we doing?

444
00:15:46.345 --> 00:15:48.075
I don't know. Brick.

445
00:15:48.147 --> 00:15:50.192
All I know is we have to have
fun. lots and lots of fun.

446
00:15:50.216 --> 00:15:51.946
and then rub their noses in it.

447
00:15:52.018 --> 00:15:53.418
Come on. there's got to
be something

448
00:15:53.486 --> 00:15:55.421
that you can share with me
that we can bond over.

449
00:15:55.488 --> 00:15:57.150
you know. like an anecdote
or a secret

450
00:15:57.223 --> 00:15:58.885
that you wouldn't tell
anybody else...

451
00:15:58.958 --> 00:16:01.018
Preferably something
we can be laughing about

452
00:16:01.093 --> 00:16:02.857
when we walk back through
that door.

453
00:16:02.929 --> 00:16:05.296
I got a B-plus
on my geometry test.

454
00:16:05.364 --> 00:16:07.458
[Sighs] Yawn.
Come on. "wow" me. Brick.

455
00:16:07.533 --> 00:16:10.731
- I was reading a book about...
- Don't even.

456
00:16:10.803 --> 00:16:12.738
Am I being kidnapped
and used as a pawn?

457
00:16:12.805 --> 00:16:15.206
'Cause I'm really confused
about what's happening here.

458
00:16:15.274 --> 00:16:17.800
[Sighs]

459
00:16:17.877 --> 00:16:20.244
I'm sorry. Brick.

460
00:16:20.313 --> 00:16:21.440
[Sighs]

461
00:16:21.514 --> 00:16:23.779
It's just that your dad and Axl

462
00:16:23.850 --> 00:16:26.376
are like two little peas
in a pod.

463
00:16:26.452 --> 00:16:28.250
and. well. I don't know.

464
00:16:28.321 --> 00:16:30.085
Lately. I've just been feeling

465
00:16:30.156 --> 00:16:33.024
like there's no room for me
in that pod. like I'm out.

466
00:16:33.092 --> 00:16:35.288
You know. I'm...
I'm invisible to the family.

467
00:16:35.361 --> 00:16:36.920
Oh. I know.

468
00:16:36.996 --> 00:16:38.464
No. no. no.
This is different.

469
00:16:38.531 --> 00:16:40.056
Is it?

470
00:16:40.132 --> 00:16:42.431
They didn't bring me food
from Taco Jason's either.

471
00:16:42.502 --> 00:16:45.768
But I sucked it up. had a bowl
of mayonnaise. and went to bed.

472
00:16:48.341 --> 00:16:50.776
Mom. can I give you some advice?

473
00:16:50.843 --> 00:16:53.972
As a person who's been
shoved aside and ignored

474
00:16:54.046 --> 00:16:55.446
most of his life.

475
00:16:55.515 --> 00:16:58.007
I realized it's important
not to dwell on the negative.

476
00:16:58.084 --> 00:17:00.110
If I let stuff get me down.

477
00:17:00.186 --> 00:17:02.018
like having only one friend

478
00:17:02.088 --> 00:17:04.819
or everybody missing
all my birthdays

479
00:17:04.891 --> 00:17:07.383
or having no one show up to
my parent-teacher conferences

480
00:17:07.460 --> 00:17:08.951
or everybody rolling their eye...

481
00:17:09.028 --> 00:17:10.189
Okay. I got it. Brick.

482
00:17:10.263 --> 00:17:12.528
I don't take it personally.

483
00:17:12.598 --> 00:17:16.000
The truth is.
if you go through life

484
00:17:16.068 --> 00:17:18.469
expecting other people
to make things good for you.

485
00:17:18.538 --> 00:17:20.131
you're gonna be disappointed.

486
00:17:20.206 --> 00:17:23.472
And the only person you can
depend on is yourself.

487
00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:27.105
And I guess I'm lucky
'cause I like myself.

488
00:17:27.179 --> 00:17:29.478
So whenever I'm with myself.
I'm happy.

489
00:17:29.549 --> 00:17:31.245
I've never once let myself down.

490
00:17:31.317 --> 00:17:32.979
[Sighs]

491
00:17:33.052 --> 00:17:34.577
I have.

492
00:17:34.854 --> 00:17:38.450
All right. Well. that's
something to work on.

493
00:17:38.524 --> 00:17:41.016
Now. let's say we go
get you that burger.

494
00:17:41.093 --> 00:17:44.996
♪♪♪♪

495
00:17:45.064 --> 00:17:46.396
[Knock on door]

496
00:17:46.465 --> 00:17:49.128
Oh. my God.
Sue. how are you?

497
00:17:49.201 --> 00:17:52.933
Or more importantly. how am I?
Thanks for asking. I'm great.

498
00:17:53.005 --> 00:17:54.871
- Oh. really?
- Oh. better than great.

499
00:17:54.941 --> 00:17:56.500
After we carried you to the car.

500
00:17:56.576 --> 00:17:58.340
the crisis had
sort of bonded us.

501
00:17:58.411 --> 00:18:01.404
So I asked Luke if he wanted to
grab a drink. and he said yes.

502
00:18:01.480 --> 00:18:03.312
- Ooh!
- Ha! So we went down the street

503
00:18:03.382 --> 00:18:05.351
to Eskimo Joe's.
and we talked for hours.

504
00:18:05.418 --> 00:18:07.046
[Gasps]
Oh. my God! Brad!

505
00:18:07.119 --> 00:18:09.520
Oh. that is so great.
Oh. I'm so happy for you.

506
00:18:09.589 --> 00:18:11.285
Luke seems like
a really nice guy.

507
00:18:11.357 --> 00:18:14.327
Oh. he is. And I was able to be
myself and everything.

508
00:18:14.393 --> 00:18:17.386
So. anyway. you are finally
free to cut Aidan loose.

509
00:18:17.463 --> 00:18:21.901
Actually. I'm not
so sure about that.

510
00:18:21.968 --> 00:18:23.493
Wait. What?

511
00:18:23.569 --> 00:18:26.164
Yeah. I don't know.
He kissed me tonight.

512
00:18:26.238 --> 00:18:28.639
and I have to say.
it wasn't so much "eh."

513
00:18:28.908 --> 00:18:31.139
It was more like "ahh."

514
00:18:31.210 --> 00:18:34.044
And that's not
the head injury talking?

515
00:18:34.113 --> 00:18:37.948
No. no. the thing is. I realized
Aidan is just like me.

516
00:18:38.017 --> 00:18:41.454
He tries really hard like me.
He's klutzy like me.

517
00:18:41.520 --> 00:18:44.012
Mm.
Maybe this is like one
of those romantic-comedy movies

518
00:18:44.090 --> 00:18:46.582
when I am pining away
after the unobtainable guy

519
00:18:46.659 --> 00:18:50.027
when the perfect guy is right
under my nose the whole time.

520
00:18:50.096 --> 00:18:52.463
[Sighs] I-I feel like
I should give Aidan a chance.

521
00:18:52.531 --> 00:18:54.227
Wow.

522
00:18:54.300 --> 00:18:57.361
[Chuckles] I'm dating Luke.
you're dating Aidan.

523
00:18:57.436 --> 00:19:00.099
This is the beginning
of "Bruke" and "Saidan."

524
00:19:00.172 --> 00:19:02.038
Ooh.
[Gasps] That's too
much like Satan.

525
00:19:02.108 --> 00:19:03.337
I'll work on it.

526
00:19:03.409 --> 00:19:05.071
"Aidue."

527
00:19:05.144 --> 00:19:07.113
Oh. Ooh. That's good.

528
00:19:07.179 --> 00:19:08.670
Ahh!

529
00:19:08.948 --> 00:19:10.348
Mmm! Okay.

530
00:19:10.416 --> 00:19:12.009
That was pretty good.

531
00:19:12.084 --> 00:19:14.019
but I still want to try
the holey burger place.

532
00:19:14.086 --> 00:19:16.131
Yeah. Maybe. next time.
we don't drive around so long

533
00:19:16.155 --> 00:19:17.515
that when we get there
it's closed.

534
00:19:17.556 --> 00:19:18.649
Mm.

535
00:19:18.724 --> 00:19:20.454
Oh. yeah. right over here.

536
00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:23.254
What's this?

537
00:19:23.329 --> 00:19:24.524
I got you a little something.

538
00:19:24.597 --> 00:19:26.259
You got me a piece
of birthday cake?

539
00:19:26.332 --> 00:19:28.324
No. I got you seven...

540
00:19:28.401 --> 00:19:32.202
[Chuckles] one for every
birthday I've missed.

541
00:19:32.271 --> 00:19:35.935
♪♪ Happy birthday to you ♪♪

542
00:19:36.008 --> 00:19:39.274
♪♪ Happy birthday to you ♪♪

543
00:19:39.345 --> 00:19:43.339
♪♪ Happy birthday. dear Brick ♪♪

544
00:19:43.416 --> 00:19:46.614
♪♪ Happy birthday to you ♪♪

545
00:19:46.686 --> 00:19:48.518
[Applause. laughter]

546
00:19:48.587 --> 00:19:50.488
[Blowing]

547
00:19:52.324 --> 00:19:55.658
You know. Brick. I may have
blown some birthdays.

548
00:19:55.728 --> 00:19:58.459
but you're never ignored
in my heart.

549
00:19:58.531 --> 00:20:00.466
I know.

550
00:20:00.533 --> 00:20:02.661
All right.

551
00:20:02.735 --> 00:20:04.260
Do I have to have
the carrot cake?

552
00:20:04.336 --> 00:20:05.565
I'm not a fan.

553
00:20:05.638 --> 00:20:07.129
No. We'll just eat
the frosting off it

554
00:20:07.206 --> 00:20:08.674
and take it home
to your dad and Axl.

555
00:20:08.741 --> 00:20:10.266
[Both chuckle]

556
00:20:10.342 --> 00:20:11.420
- Ooh. I want...
- Let's see.

557
00:20:11.444 --> 00:20:13.003
- Try that one?
- Yes.

558
00:20:13.079 --> 00:20:15.139
- I'll try this one.
- All right. It's colorful.

559
00:20:15.214 --> 00:20:19.049
Axl. come on! Let's go!
Game starts in 15 minutes.

560
00:20:19.118 --> 00:20:20.711
Sorry. Dad.
Lexie just called.

561
00:20:20.786 --> 00:20:23.017
and she's back from Colorado.
See ya!

562
00:20:23.089 --> 00:20:25.718
[Television playing]

563
00:20:31.697 --> 00:20:33.097
Here.

564
00:20:36.769 --> 00:20:38.431
- Okay.
- [Sighs]

565
00:20:38.504 --> 00:20:40.063
This is "Outlander."

566
00:20:40.139 --> 00:20:42.335
I'm pretty deep into it.
but I think you can catch up.

567
00:20:42.408 --> 00:20:44.741
That's Claire.
and she's a World War Il nurse

568
00:20:44.810 --> 00:20:48.713
who magically falls
through stones into
1770-something England.

569
00:20:48.781 --> 00:20:50.716
How can she fall through stones?

570
00:20:50.783 --> 00:20:52.274
They're not porous.

571
00:20:52.351 --> 00:20:54.513
Some women do a fairy dance.
and it just happens.

572
00:20:54.587 --> 00:20:56.146
Just watch it.
You'll like it.

573
00:20:56.222 --> 00:20:58.350
There's battle scenes.
and men fight with swords.

574
00:21:00.259 --> 00:21:01.979
<i>Frankie: You know. it's silly
to get jealous</i>

575
00:21:02.061 --> 00:21:03.359
<i>of people in your family.</i>

576
00:21:03.429 --> 00:21:05.227
<i>So they love each other
more one week.</i>

577
00:21:05.297 --> 00:21:07.027
<i>You know. the next week.</i>

578
00:21:07.099 --> 00:21:08.477
<i>they're just gonna do something
to piss each other off.</i>

579
00:21:08.501 --> 00:21:10.800
<i>But the point is.
I played it cool.</i>

580
00:21:11.070 --> 00:21:13.062
<i>and now I have my husband back.</i>

581
00:21:13.139 --> 00:21:14.607
♪♪♪♪

582
00:21:14.673 --> 00:21:18.166
Do you have to sit so close?
There's a whole big couch here.

583
00:21:18.244 --> 00:21:21.373
Captions by VITAC...
